story.title: Fatal Consequences - Episode 5
story.storyDescription: Jo-Jo awakens, trapped in the wreckage of her car, covered in blood. The last 48 hours of her life are a blank, and the dead man beside her . . . is a total stranger.

messages.text: One day later, Jo-Jo arrives at Walter and Izabel Leighton‚Äôs mansion.
She straightens her conservative suit and rings the doorbell, bracing for her conversation with the Senator.
But he isn‚Äôt the one who answers‚Ä¶
Hello!
I‚Äôm sorry‚Ä¶I was expecting Senator Leighton.
I thought so. Walter must have double-booked again.
I‚Äôll call to reschedule.
Oh, no. Come inside! He won‚Äôt be long. You‚Äôre Carole, aren‚Äôt you?
No, I‚Äôm her colleague‚Ä¶Joan.
So many people working PR for Walter‚Äôs new campaign!
Carole might not have mentioned me.
Even so, I‚Äôm terrible with names. Walter is always getting mad at me.
When will the senator be back?
I‚Äôm not sure. I wasn‚Äôt supposed to be here today.
Oh?
I just flew in from Milan. The collections were very disappointing, so I decided to end my trip early.
What a shame.
Izabel shrugs a tanned shoulder.
It‚Äôs okay. I‚Äôm going to New York in an hour.
What is it the British say? Keep calm and carry on shopping!
I won‚Äôt keep you.
No, please come in. Jane was it?
Joan.
Joan, right, sorry.
Perhaps Senator Leighton got stuck in a committee meeting.
I can check with Walter‚Äôs assistant. Please come in.
Jo decides to play along. Even if the senator returns, she doubts he‚Äôll blow her cover.
That would be kind of you.
Can I get you something cold to drink?
I don‚Äôt want to put you to any trouble.
It‚Äôs no trouble at all. We have loads of fresh juice.
I wanted Walter to try a cleansing detox, but he‚Äôs such a man about those things. So pigheaded!
Apple? Orange? Carrot?
Apple, please.
I‚Äôll be right back! Make yourself at home.
Izabel exits to the kitchen, returning with a tall glass of apple juice.
Jo-Jo takes a sip.
Thanks. This really is delicious.
I‚Äôm so glad you like it.
You have a lovely voice, Mrs. Leighton. Do I detect an accent?
Yes, was born in Brazil.
Really? How did you meet Senator Leighton?
You PR types are so curious!
That‚Äôs what makes us good at our jobs.
I was in the Miss Universe Pageant. I met Walter at a fundraiser.
The senator was smitten.
Love at first sight, he said. But that was 20 years ago.
How romantic. I‚Ä¶I‚Ä¶
Is something wrong, Joan?
I feel a bit dizzy.
Jo-Jo slumps over as Mrs. Leighton takes the glass from her hand.
Yes, GHB will do that to you.
Jo-Jo‚Äôs phone pings. It‚Äôs Senator Leighton.
Your minion wants to reschedule.
Izabel reads the text on Jo-Jo‚Äôs phone, and then speaks to the unconscious body in front of her.
You were right. He was held up in committee.
Let me answer that for you.
Laughing, Izabel replies to the senator‚Äôs text on Jo-Jo‚Äôs phone.
Too bad Mistress won‚Äôt live to make that appointment.
Many hours later, Jo-Jo awakens. It‚Äôs dark outside. She‚Äôs tied to a chair.
Izabel Leighton sits across from her, holding a gun.
Finally!
Mrs. Leighton?
Miss Avery.
You know who I am?
Of course. You‚Äôve caused me a great deal of trouble, Jo-Jo.
But I guess I should thank you.
What for?
For saving me the trouble of getting rid of Forrester.
Forrester?
Shall I give you a second to put all the pieces together?
You?
I hired him, he hired you, and here we are.
You must want your husband out of the race very badly.
Out of the race? Not at all!
I want him to win.
Why?
Because when he‚Äôs president, he‚Äôll do everything I tell him to.
You‚Äôre blackmailing your own husband?
I‚Äôve got some very interesting plans for this country.
He‚Äôll never go along with them.
Yes he will. The Leighton legacy means everything to him.
A president with a mistress is one thing, but one who licks a pair of kinky boots while being flogged?
Jo-Jo realizes the cross is still around her neck. She may have a chance.
Keeping her face neutral, she responds.
You have no proof.
Izabel aims the gun at Jo-Jo‚Äôs kneecap.
I‚Äôll start by shooting there. You‚Äôll volunteer the information, eventually.
Santa do Pau oco‚Ä¶Vai te fuder, porra!
You speak Portuguese. How nice!
A man walks into the room.
What did she say?
Oh, hello, darling. She says I‚Äôm someone who only plays at being good.
She also suggests I go screw myself.
Dr. Dante? What the hell are you doing here?
Miss Avery, I think you‚Äôve met my lover?
Dante gives Izabel a deep kiss.
He moves to Jo-Jo and removes her pendant. He takes out the USB and shows it to Izabel.
Here‚Äôs what you‚Äôre after. I‚Äôll keep it safe for us.
He slips it into his pocket.
What? How did you two get together?
She came to me for a cosmetic procedure. One thing led to another.
Luther‚Äôs the only man who‚Äôs ever seen the real me.
What can I say? She‚Äôs charming. Brilliant. A tigress in bed‚Ä¶
I fell in love with her.
And I with you, meu amor, but now, we must dispose of Miss Avery.
Izabel points the gun at Jo-Jo‚Äôs heart. Casually, Dante steps in the line of fire.
Allow me to do the honors?
Smiling, Izabel hands him the gun.
Perfect.
Suddenly, the door crashes open. Quinn bursts into the room.
Damn it, Dante! What are you thinking?
Quinn draws his weapon.
Luther!
I love you, Izabel, but I can‚Äôt let you go through with it.
Dante turns his gun on Izabel.
It was one thing passing along intel to your South American cronies, but this is just too big.
Bastard!
Izabel lunges for her gun. It goes off, firing into the ceiling. Quinn shoots her dead.
Izabel, NO!
Dante drops his gun.
Dante, are you all right?
I never meant for it to end this way. I‚Äôm so sorry, Izabel.
When did you figure out she hired Forrester?
The last time we made love. About a week ago.
A week ago?!
Yes. She told me her husband was being blackmailed. Gave me details.
But that was‚Ä¶
Before I met with the senator.
Right. Only someone who was in on it could have known.
Luther, you should have told us immediately.
I know, but I thought if I could just bring her in myself, make things right‚Ä¶
She‚Äôd still have spent the rest of her life in prison.
And blamed me for all of it. I know.
Quinn‚Äôs face softens.
You truly loved her.
Yes, but after I found out she paid Forrester to kill someone‚Äî
I couldn‚Äôt look the other way.
I‚Äôm not sure how The Agency‚Äôs going to handle things from here.
Of course I take full responsibility for my actions. Whatever happens, happens.
Dante hands the USB to Quinn.
I‚Äôll make arrangements for her. My last act for The Agency.
He gently lifts Izabel in his arms.
Goodbye, Jo-Jo. Good luck.
Dante carries Izabel‚Äôs body out.
Why didn‚Äôt he stop her sooner?
It was partly love, but also‚Äî
He couldn‚Äôt risk the recording falling into the wrong hands.
Hers or anyone else‚Äôs.
Exactly.
Quinn unties Jo-Jo.
What happens to me now?
That‚Äôs undecided. The agency could use someone with your specialized skill set.
Interesting proposition.
You might look good in a white hat.
You know, I was really thinking of retiring, but I‚Äôd consider your offer‚Äî
Depending on the job description.
You‚Äôd be working directly under me.
Funny, that‚Äôs exactly what I had in mind.
